Anders Lindegaard: Preston sign West Brom goalkeeper on loan
Championship side Preston North End have signed goalkeeper Anders Lindegaard on loan from West Bromwich Albion for the remainder of the season.Denmark international Lindegaard, 31, has played only one League Cup game since joining the Baggies on a free transfer from Manchester United.United have chosen to recall Sam Johnstone, who started Saturday's 3-1 home defeat by Brentford at Deepdale.Lindegaard could make his Preston debut at Derby on 2 February.Find all the latest football transferson our dedicated page.